  "prompt": "What is potassium sorbate?",
  "response": "Potassium sorbate is a chemical compound commonly used as a preservative in food, beverages, and cosmetic products. It is the potassium salt of sorbic acid and is known for its ability to inhibit the growth of mold, yeast, and some bacteria, thus extending the shelf life of products. \n\nIn food applications, potassium sorbate is often found in products such as dairy items, baked goods, beverages, and some types of sauces. It is considered safe for consumption within established limits by regulatory agencies, such as the FDA and the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA).\n\nIn addition to its use in food, potassium sorbate is also used in personal care products, such as lotions and shampoos, to prevent microbial growth. It is often listed in ingredient labels simply as \"potassium sorbate.\"",
